    "body": "note that this doesn't reduce gas costs across the board, since due to peculiarities in the ABI design, leaving the bytes in calldata requires multiple dereferences in order to access it, which is a bytecode and gas tradeoff. if you access the same bytes multiple times, leaving the bytes in calldata could result in worse performance.",
